ej,olivg101,P,lands901,Call at HP (Threw glove) $Gene Oliver and Dick Groat collided at HP; Groat called safe; as Oliver argued the call the ball rolled away and Jerry Buchek advanced to 3B; Oliver ejected by HP umpire Stan Landes; Oliver threw his mitt into the air and left the field only to return moments later with his gear as if he was going to continue playing; Landes 'ejected' him again; Cardinals manager Red Schoendienst argued with Landes that Braves manager Bobby Bragan had visited his pitcher twice in the inning and the pitcher should be removed; when Landes disagreed, Scheondienst protested the game1965SLN.EVN.regular.comment.csv"
